thread.title: Grain lower livestock mixed

title: Grain lower livestock mixed
text:
Wed, Aug 12, 2015, 1:20 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 8 hrs 40 mins Grain lower livestock mixed Grain mixed on the CBOT, beef and pork mixed on the CME Associated Press – 29 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were lower in early trading Thursday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for September delivery lost 16.50 cents to $5.09 a bushel; December corn was 12.25 cents lower at $3.8860 a bushel; December oats were 5 cents lower at $2.4260 bushel; while November soybeans lost 14.50 cents to 9.80 cents a bushel. 
Beef mixed and pork were mixed on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. 
October live cattle was .03 cent lower at $1.4928 a pound; August feeder cattle was .55 cent higher at $2.1480 a pound; October lean hogs lost .55 cent to $.6243 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Annual cattle quota plan put to Jakarta AAP
